video_name: JD Vance says Kamala Harris is 'a million times worse' than Joe Biden
title: WCNC
description:
Republican vice presidential nominee JD Vance used his first solo campaign rallies Monday to throw fresh barbs at Vice President Kamala Harris a day after President Joe Biden threw the presidential election into upheaval by dropping out and endorsing his second-in-command to lead Democrats against Donald Trump.

The Ohio senator campaigned at his former high school in Middletown before an evening stop in Radford, Virginia, two venues intended to play up his conservative populist appeal across the Rust Belt and small-town America that he said the Biden-Harris administration has forgotten.

“History will remember Joe Biden as not just a quitter, which he is, but as one of the worst presidents in the history of the United States of America," Vance said in Virginia. “But my friends, Kamala Harris is a million times worse and everybody knows it. She signed up for every single one of Joe Biden’s failures, and she lied about his mental capacity to serve as president.”

Vance sought to saddle Harris with the administration’s record on inflation and immigration, clarifying the lines of attack that the Trump campaign will use even with the change at the top of the Democratic ticket. Harris still must be formally nominated but has quickly consolidated commitments from top party leaders and is now backed by more than half of the delegates needed to win her party’s nomination vote, according to an Associated Press survey.

“The border crisis is a Kamala Harris crisis," Vance said, accusing Biden and Harris together of rolling back immigration policies that Trump enacted in his White House term. He added Harris is “even more extreme than Biden” because, Vance alleged, she has designs on abolishing federal immigration enforcement and domestic police forces. #Politics #Election #News

video_name: VP Candidate J.D. Vance Targets Harris At First Rally In Middleton High School | India Today Global
title: India Today Global
description:
A rally was held at J.D. Vance's former high school, where Vance expressed his displeasure with Kamala Harris's presidential nomination. He criticized Harris for discussing American history with condemnation, emphasizing that a great leader should feel gratitude toward their country. Vance also voiced concerns about the manner of President Biden's withdrawal, describing it as a threat to democracy, and stated that the Republican Party fights for democracy every single day. He accused the media of lying about Trump, whom he described as a family man. Additionally, Vance discussed the popular perception of Middletown as backward, countering that Middletown is the source of America's greatness. He promised to restore "an America that works for Americans."

Jennifer Aniston is sharing her disbelief for Republican Vice-Presidential nominee J.D. Vance’s past comments about “childless” women. After a clip of Donald Trump’s running mate from 2021 resurfaced on social media in which he claims that United States is being run by “childless cat ladies who are miserable at their own lives and choices that they made,” the “Friends” star took to her Instagram story to call him out. “I truly can’t believe this is coming from a potential VP of The United States,” the actress wrote on Wednesday, adding, “All I can say is: Mr. Vance, I pray that your daughter is fortunate enough to bear children of her own one day. I hope she will not need to turn to IVF as a second option. Because you are trying to take that away from her, too.” The “Morning Show” star does not have any children and got candid in a December cover story in 2022 with Allure that she tried to get pregnant for many years but struggled with fertility and IVF.

video_name: ‘She lied’: JD Vance hits out at Kamala Harris during Virginia rally
title: Sky News Australia
description:
Republican vice presidential nominee JD Vance has hit out at US Vice President Kamala Harris during a rally in Radford, Virginia.

“She signed up for every single one of Joe Biden’s failures, and she lied about his mental capacity to serve as President,” he said.

“Our country has been saddled for three and a half years with a President who cannot do the job, and that is all because Kamala Harris and the rest of the Democrats lied about his ability to be our President.”

video_name: JD Vance says Kamala Harris is a ‘threat to Democracy’ because voters won’t decide Dem nominee
title: New York Post
description:
Republican veep nominee JD Vance said Monday that Vice President Kamala Harris is a “threat to Democracy” because she will likely be chosen as the Democratic presidential nominee without voter input.

The senator, speaking in Ohio at his first solo rally after being selected as Donald Trump’s running mate, argued that Trump made his “case to voters” and was nominated as the GOP presidential nominee despite “good competition.”

If Harris is named the Democratic nominee to replace President Biden without voter input, that thwarts the Democratic process, Vance said.

title: Indisputable with Dr. Rashad Richey
description:
J.D. Vance faced backlash after calling Kamala Harris a "childless cat lady" during an interview with Tucker Carlson. Dr. Rashad Richey and Yasmin Aliya Khan discuss on Indisputable. Tell us what you think in the comments below.

Read more here: https://meidasnews.com/news/vance-calls-harris-a-miserable-childless-cat-lady

"The political problem that Donald Trump has with his running mate JD Vance is that he doesn't attract a single voter outside the MAGA base. You could argue he's even more consistently MAGA that Trump himself. His rhetoric and boorishness especially turns off the female voters that sent Trump packing in 2020.

When you compare the results by voting demographics between the 2016 and 2020 elections, the various groups were remarkably consistent. However, one group stood out - suburban women. Trump did surprisingly well with suburban women voters in 2016 against Hillary Clinton, keeping things close enough to provide the margin of victory. But in 2020, Trump was crushed by those very voters by a wide margin. "

title: 10 News First
description:
U.S. Vice President Kamala Harris has lauded Joe Biden's legacy over the past three years as "unmatched in modern history" in her first public appearance since his withdrawal from the 2024 presidential race.

Harris did not specifically address in her Washington speech on Monday that she is now the leading Democratic candidate for president and has received endorsement from Biden to be his successor.

Meanwhile in Ohio, Republican vice presidential candidate J.D. Vance accused Kamala Harris, his Senate Democratic colleagues, and the media of lying about President Biden's mental capacity.

"Every single person who saw Joe Biden knew that he wasn't capable of doing the job... that is an insult to voters,” said Vance on Monday, in his hometown of Middletown.

video_name: ‘Million times worse than Biden': JD Vance's no-holds-barred attack at Kamala Harris
title: The Economic Times
description:
Republican vice-presidential nominee JD Vance took to the stage for his second solo rally of the day — and the race — Monday evening, holding back no punches against Vice President Kamala Harris, the Democratic Party’s newly anointed leader. Harris is “a million times worse” than Biden, Vance declared, and the Biden record is the “Kamala Harris record.” “If Joe Biden is not fit to run for president, he’s not fit to serve as president,” Vance added at Radford University’s Dedmon Center hours after his hometown rally in Middletown, Ohio. The southwest Virginia city is right in the middle of Appalachia — and culturally similar to where Vance grew up in Ohio and Kentucky. The crowd broke out in a “U-S-A! U-S-A!” chant when Vance talked about the need to bring manufacturing jobs back from overseas to America’s Rust Belt.

video_name: Trump Ticket: JD Vance accepts VP nomination at RNC | LiveNOW from FOX
title: LiveNOW from FOX
description:
On Wednesday, Ohio Senator JD Vance formally accepted the GOP Vice Presidential nomination, coming on Day 3 of the Republican National Convention in Milwaukee. Former President Donald Trump, who's been seen wearing a bandage on his right ear following an assassination attempt during a weekend rally in Butler, Pennsylvania, announced the pick earlier this week. Introduced by his wife, Usha Vance, the 39-year-old detailed his own life story and said, "Tonight is a night of hope. A celebration of what America once was, and with God’s grace, what it will soon be again." His speech comes on the same day that President Biden's campaign said Vice President Harris accepted a date of August 12th for a debate with Vance on CBS. The Trump campaign would not commit.

video_name: Harris slams JD Vance, Trump at North Carolina campaign event
title: Irish Times
description:
US vice president Kamala Harris slammed Donald Trump and his running mate, senator JD Vance, calling their governing plans "extreme and divisive."
  
As US president Joe Biden recuperates from Covid-19, vice-president Kamala Harris has become the standard bearer of their reelection effort, visiting the battleground states of Michigan and North Carolina this past week before headlining a well-attended fundraiser in Massachusetts on Saturday.

Harris has assumed the starring role at a time when a growing number of Democratic elected officials are pushing for her to become the party’s nominee. Both voters and donors say they have grown dissatisfied with the president, and the campaign’s fundraising efforts have sputtered. (Video: Reuters)

video_name: Vì sao Phó tướng JD Vance nhận xét bà Harris tệ hơn Tổng thống Biden triệu lần? Bầu cử Mỹ 2024
title: Tin24h
description:
#tin tức 24h #tintuc  
Phó tướng JD Vance: Bà Harris tệ hơn Tổng thống Biden triệu lần
JD Vance, ứng viên phó tổng thống tranh cử cùng ông Trump, cho rằng bà Harris "tệ hơn Tổng thống Biden triệu lần" và cả hai đều không đủ khả năng lãnh đạo đất nước.

"Giờ đây, lịch sử sẽ ghi nhớ Tổng thống Joe Biden không chỉ là người bỏ cuộc, mà còn là một trong những Tổng thống tệ nhất của nước Mỹ. Nhưng các bạn của tôi à, Phó tổng thống Kamala Harris còn tệ hơn ông ấy cả triệu lần và ai cũng biết điều này", ứng viên phó tổng thống của đảng Cộng hòa JD Vance nói trong cuộc vận động tranh cử ở thành phố Radford, bang Virginia ngày 22/7.

Ông Vance cáo buộc bà Harris ủng hộ "những thất bại" của Tổng thống Biden cũng như nói dối rằng "ông Biden đủ năng lực trí tuệ để làm tổng thống". Theo Vance, dấu ấn của bà Harris cũng giống như ông Biden và cả hai đều không phù hợp đảm đương vai trò lãnh đạo.

"Liệu ai đó có thể thừa nhận nếu Biden không đủ tiêu chuẩn để tranh cử tổng thống, thì ông ấy cũng không đủ tiêu chuẩn để làm tổng thống", ông nói. "Nếu Kamala Harris mù quáng hoặc tệ hại đến mức không thừa nhận với người dân Mỹ rằng ông Biden không bao giờ nên ngồi ở vị trí lãnh đạo, thì bà ấy cũng không đủ tư cách để trở thành lãnh đạo".

video_name: JD Vance called Kamala Harris and other Democrats “childless cat ladies”￼ on Fox News in 2021
title: Mo News
description:
#gop VP Nominee JD #vance is going viral for past comments about Vice President Kamala #harris 

In a clip from 2021, Vance told former #foxnews host Tucker #carlson that the country was run by “a bunch of childless cat ladies who are miserable at their own lives. Look at Kamala Harris, Pete Buttigieg, AOC, the entire future of the Democrats is controlled by people without children,” Vance continued. “How does it make any sense we’ve turned our country over to people who don’t really have a direct stake in it?”

On her Instagram Story Wednesday, actress Jennifer Aniston reposted the clip with the below comments.

“I truly can’t believe this is coming from a potential VP of The United States,” Aniston wrote. “All I can say is… Mr. Vance, I pray that your daughter is fortunate enough to bear children of her own one day.”.

Vance says that the "childless left" idea grew out of a conversation with a friend who noted that DC was near the top of lists of cities where adults had the fewest children.
"I was like — oh, that's really odd, right?" Vance recalled. "The city that's governing for the rest of the country is also the place that, in some ways, is the least like the rest of the country, where most people do want to have children, and most people do start families."
The childless factor, said Vance, might explain to him why so many policymakers favored school mask mandates during the pandemic. "When you have children, and you've interacted with children regularly, I think you realize how many of the left policies are really harmful to kids," he said.

video_name: Trump and Pelosi cause a heated debate between J.D. Vance and Tim Ryan | USA TODAY
title: USA TODAY
description:
In the second and final Ohio Senate debate, Republican J.D. Vance and Democrat Rep. Tim Ryan defend their ties with their party's leadership.

RELATED: Ohio Senate candidates Tim Ryan, J.D. Vance debate abortion, police https://bit.ly/3S4sSoQ

Republican J.D. Vance and Democratic U.S. Rep. Tim Ryan faced off in the hour-long debate hosted by WFMJ in Youngstown. The event was more heated and personal than last week's debate in Cleveland, in part because of a format that allowed the candidates to spar back and forth with no time limits. Vance and Ryan are vying for the Senate seat being vacated by retiring Sen. Rob Portman in the Nov. 8 election.

Both candidates kicked off the debate assuring voters that they're their own man. Vance dismissed Trump's comment that the Senate candidate is "kissing my a--" as a joke and accused Ryan of focusing his entire campaign on the quip. Ryan said Ohioans want an "a-- kicker, not an a-- kisser" at last week's debate, and his campaign created an internet meme of Trump-themed Chapstick.

Ryan, meanwhile, presented himself as independent of Democratic leadership even though he's voted with President Joe Biden's agenda 100% of the time, according to FiveThirtyEight. When Vance pointed this out, Ryan noted that he challenged Speaker Nancy Pelosi for the position of top Democrat in 2016.

video_name: "White Trash" Historian Nancy Isenberg on J.D. Vance, "Hillbilly Elegy" & Class in America
title: Democracy Now!
description:
Support our work: https://democracynow.org/donate/sm-desc-yt

American historian and the author of White Trash: The 400-Year Untold History of Class in America, Nancy Isenberg, calls Republican vice-presidential nominee J.D. Vance a peddler of the "self-made man myth." Isenberg criticizes Hilbilly Elegy, the memoir that propelled him to fame, as a deceptive way of selling this myth and the conservative politics it comes with. "Much of what his memoir says tells us nothing about real class conditions," Isenberg says, pointing to her own historical and sociological research on the rural poor in the United States.

video_name: Qui est J.D. Vance, colistier de Donald Trump choisi par le candidat républicain?
title: Radio-Canada Info
description:
Si Donald Trump, ancien président des États-Unis et candidat républicain à l'élection présidentielle américaine, est élu, J.D. Vance deviendra le vice-président des États-Unis. Ce dernier a accepté la nomination de son parti et a prononcé un discours en faveur des classes populaires américaines.

Le sénateur J.D. Vance a par ailleurs participé mercredi après-midi (17 juillet 2024) à une collecte de fonds pour sa campagne, ce qui constitue sa première apparition publique officielle à l'extérieur de la convention républicaine depuis qu'il a été désigné colistier de Donald Trump, lundi (15 juillet 2024).

Celui qui s'est notamment fait connaître pour son livre « Hillbilly Elegy », qui porte sur la désillusion de la classe ouvrière blanche dans sa ville d'enfance de Middletown en Ohio, a fait part de quelques statistiques pour dénoncer l'augmentation du coût de la vie dans cet État sous l’administration de Joe Biden.

Dans son reportage, notre correspondante Azeb Wolde-Giorghis nous présente ce politicien de 39 ans.

So right now, talk is swirling all over the internet, all over the media that President Biden, uh, is likely to drop out of the race. He may drop out this weekend, he may drop out early next week. He may not drop out at all. We all know nobody knows what's happening, and nobody is happier about that than the Trump campaign, because the Trump campaign is actually using this. Will he or won't he about President Biden as an excuse to prevent JD Vance from agreeing to any vice presidential debates. Now, vice President Kamala Harris has already agreed to several different dates where we could have a vice presidential debate. She said, we can do it July 23rd. We can do it August 12th, August 13th. I'm ready. Let's go. Harris says, and the Trump campaign issued a statement saying, quote, we don't know who the Democrat nominee for vice president is going to be. 

So we, we can't lock in a date before their convention to do so, would be unfair to Gavin Newsom, JB Pritzker, Gretchen Whitmer, or whoever Kamala Harris picks as her running mate. Oh, we wanna be fair, right? We, we don't wanna put a Gavin Newsom or a Pritzker or Whitmer in a position. You know, we, we don't wanna make decisions for those people because that's just so incredibly rude. Well, guess what? At least as of this recording, the Vice presidential candidate is Kamala Harris. So why don't you just go ahead and plan on debating her if that changes over the weekend. Change the thing. Like, that's all you gotta do. You just say, okay, well, we'll do this instead. It's not that difficult. You could easily do that. Yes, JD Vance is highly educated, okay? I am not denying that he is an intelligent person. I, I do think he is. He is one of the few Republicans that I do think has a, a pretty solid grasp, you know, on intellect. He is also an opportunist. He's also a bit of a conman, in my opinion, just like Donald Trump, you know, going whichever way the wind blows, whichever suits him politically, which is why he had that about face and now loves Trump as opposed to hating him a few years ago. But the campaign must see something that the public is not aware of, something that they wanna hide, something that they wanna protect JD Vance from exposing about him himself. If he gets up there on a debate stage, it doesn't matter who the nominee is gonna be, it doesn't matter at all. You could go ahead and agree to a debate. You could say, okay, 

Well, if Biden's not the nominee, how about we just go ahead and set a date for September? It'll be after the Democratic Convention. There'll be no question about it then. So September 1st, second, third, fourth, fifth, you can pick any date in September. You could pick a date in October, but y'all won't do it, and you're trying to blame it on the Democrats because clearly you're trying to protect JD Vance from himself, and I can't wait to find out why.

video_name: JD Vance News | Usha Vance Is Fourth Person Of South Asian Descent In The 2024 Campaign | N18G
title: CNN-News18
description:
The announcement of Ohio Senator JD Vance as Donald Trump's running mate, has made Asian American voters very hopeful. And it's because of Vance's Indian Origin wife Usha Chilukuri. The 38-year-old Yale graduate is the daughter of Indian immigrants. As she joins the Trump campaign, Asian Americans hope the increase in representation will correspond with a push to connect with a voting bloc that has long been overlooked. Asian Americans are the fastest-growing racial or ethnic group of eligible voters in the United States. The Trump campaign is hoping that Usha Vance could appeal to minority voters. The 2024 presidential campaign has seen three politicians of South Asian descent vying for the White House: Former South Carolina Gov. Nikki Haley and entrepreneur Vivek Ramaswamy both competed during the Republican primaries, while Vice President Kamala Harris is running for a second term with President Joe Biden.

video_name: JD Vance: Kamala Harris Should Stop Condescension & Listen to Constituents
title: JD Vance for Senate
description:
Ohio U.S. Senate candidate JD Vance joined Brian Kilmeade on Fox & Friends to discuss Vice President Kamala Harris’s out-of-touch comments about rural communities and voter ID requirements.

“I think that Kamala Harris, like a lot of folks who come from our elite class, they have this stereotype of small town America that it’s all backwards and people don’t have the basic things that they need. But if you talk to people, you talk to Ohioans, or if you just read a poll you find out that rural Americans are actually strongly in favor of voter ID.

“So I think the Kamala Harris’s of the world should leave their condescension to their staffers and actually listen to what their constituents are saying. Because those people are saying we actually want voter ID. We want safe and secure elections. Let us figure out how to accomplish that.”

----

Click the RED BUTTON to SUBSCRIBE to JD Vance’s official YouTube channel.

WEBSITE: jdvance.com

Follow us on social media!!
FACEBOOK: https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100070055152736
TWITTER: https://twitter.com/JDVance1 & https://twitter.com/JDVancePress
INSTAGRAM: https://www.instagram.com/teamjdvance/
GETTR: https://www.gettr.com/user/jdvance1

----

Conservative Outsider. Marine. Businessman. Author.

JD grew up in Middletown, Ohio, a once flourishing American manufacturing town where Ohioans could actually live a middle-class life. But over time, he witnessed jobs and economic opportunities slowly disappear from the community, leaving family, friends, and neighbors with nothing.

Turbulence was common at home and at school. JD’s father left home when he was a young boy. His mother struggled with drug addiction his entire life. His grandmother, called Mamaw, was his saving grace. Her tough love and discipline kept him on the straight and narrow. That, or maybe the fact that she owned 19 handguns. She taught him the importance of being grounded in faith and family and the prospect that a better life lay ahead.

JD went on to serve our nation in the Iraq War as a proud Marine, graduated from The Ohio State University, received his law degree from Yale Law School, and became a successful investor in Silicon Valley. He wrote a bestselling book, Hillbilly Elegy, which was turned into a movie on Netflix.

After the success of his book, JD became a well-known commentator. On conservative and liberal networks, JD fiercely defended working-class Americans and the conservative way of life that values grit, determination, and freedom. JD is now a fixture on Fox News Channel, Newsmax, and other outlets.

JD moved back to Ohio in 2017. He has seen firsthand livelihoods devastated by job loss, addiction, economic turmoil and so much more. He started a business in Cincinnati and has focused on growing companies that create well-paying jobs. His business experience taught him firsthand that so many American companies struggle with unfair competition from China and from their own government, which often rewards multinational technology firms over Ohio small businesses.

video_name: Former President Trump picks JD Vance as running mate: What to know about the Senator from Ohio
title: WKYC Channel 3
description:
Ohio U.S. Sen J.D. Vance has been named the Republican nominee for Vice President of the United States, chosen by former President Donald Trump as his running mate in the 2024 presidential election. It marks the first time in 1944 that an Ohio native has been on a presidential ticket, and also leads to speculation regarding the future of his Senate seat.

Of course, if the Trump-Vance ticket loses to the Democratic duo of current President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris in November, Vance will almost certainly return to Congress, where he won't be up for reelection until 2028. But if Trump wins a second nonconsecutive term and Vance ascends to within a heartbeat of the nation's highest office, someone will have to replace him in the Senate, and there are several laws reflecting how that process must take place.

Here's a look at the rules for naming a successor: https://www.wkyc.com/article/news/local/ohio/what-will-happen-if-ohio-us-sen-jd-vance-becomes-vice-president-rules-for-naming-successor/95-20d2ad65-28b7-4c26-9d41-005b0e50ae5a --

title: Cyrus
description:
Vice President Kamala Harris has been actively challenging the Republican Party and former President Donald Trump, recently shifting her focus to Sen. JD Vance, Trump's likely VP pick. 

Concerns about President Biden's viability have put Harris in the spotlight, with some Democrats considering her as a potential presidential candidate. Harris views Vance as a formidable debate opponent, particularly on issues like reproductive rights and Trump's threat to democracy.

Biden's recent debate performance has intensified discussions about his ability to lead, with some Democrats urging him to step down. A poll shows 6 in 10 Democrats believe Harris would make a good president, while 65% think Biden should drop out. On the campaign trail, Harris focuses on Trump, using Vance as an example of Trump's extreme agenda, particularly on abortion. Despite insider discussions, Harris publicly supports Biden and emphasizes party unity. Her campaign message aims to keep Trump and his allies on the defensive, making the 2024 race one to watch closely. Stay tuned for more updates!

video_name: VP Kamala #harris says JD #vance speech at RNC didn’t tell full story. Calls him & #trump divisive￼
title: Mo News
description:
Vice President Kamala Harris on Thursday laced into the newly formed Republican presidential ticket, casting former President Donald Trump and Sen. JD Vance of Ohio as purveyors of “extreme” and “divisive” plans who would undermine the middle class.

Her trip to Fayetteville, N.C., was her first campaign appearance since Vance formally accepted a spot on the Republican ticket at his party’s convention a day earlier, and her speech was in some ways an initial effort to define her new opponent, who has emphasized his working-class roots.

“It’s a compelling story — and it was not the full story,” she said of his speech on Wednesday night, adding that Americans were “not buying” claims from Trump that “he and his running mate are going to prioritize the middle class” and unify the country.

video_name: Ohio US Senate race: JD Vance gives victory speech after defeating Tim Ryan
title: WKYC Channel 3
description:
Ohio's open US Senate seat will remain in Republican hands.

NBC News projects Republican JD Vance, a venture capitalist and best-selling "Hillbilly Elegy" author, has defeated longtime Democratic U.S. Rep. Tim Ryan in the race to succeed retiring Sen. Rob Portman. With the Senate currently at an even 50-50 between Republicans and Democrats (with Vice President Kamala Harris able to break ties), this race took on added importance across the nation.

"We just got a great chance to govern, and we need to use it," Vance told his supporters Tuesday night after Ryan "graciously" called him to concede. "I promise to all of my friends who are going to be at the Statehouse, to all of my friends who are going to be at the State Capitol, we need better leadership in Washington, D.C. And that's exactly what I promised: To fight for you every single day."

video_name: Kamala Harris Criticizes Trump's VP Pick J.D. Vance
title: OFF TOPIC SHOW
description:
Kamala Harris Criticizes Trump's VP Pick J.D. Vance: A Rubber Stamp for Trump's Extreme Agenda

In a recent video, Vice President Kamala Harris has expressed strong criticism of former President Donald Trump's choice for vice president, Senator J.D. Vance. Harris accused Vance of being a "rubber stamp" for Trump's "extreme" agenda and warned that if elected, Vance would help implement the controversial Project 2025 plan for a second Trump term. This plan has been described as extreme and includes targeting critical programs like Head Start and Medicare.

Harris's comments come after Trump announced Vance as his running mate, a decision that has sparked debate and controversy. The Vice President emphasized the importance of electing leaders who prioritize the well-being of the country and its citizens over loyalty to a single individual. She called on voters to reject Trump's agenda and the potential implementation of Project 2025, which she believes would have detrimental effects on the nation.

The video was released as part of the ongoing political discourse surrounding the upcoming presidential election and the role of the vice presidency. Harris's remarks highlight the stark differences in vision and approach between the Biden-Harris administration and a potential second Trump term.

video_name: JD Vance on our Civilizational Crisis
title: Intercollegiate Studies Institute
description:
Join us for an enlightening and thought-provoking speech by J.D. Vance, author of the bestselling memoir "Hillbilly Elegy" and U.S. Senator, as he delves into the complexities of the American Dream and the civilizational crisis facing our nation today. Hosted by the Intercollegiate Studies Institute (ISI), this event brings together students, educators, and thought leaders to explore the pressing issues affecting our society and the future of our country.

In this powerful address, Vance discusses the evolving concept of the American Dream and its impact on different communities. He examines the economic, cultural, and social challenges contributing to our current civilizational crisis, drawing on his personal experiences and insights from "Hillbilly Elegy." Vance also explores potential solutions and the role of individuals and communities in restoring the American Dream.

Don't miss this opportunity to gain valuable perspectives from one of today's most influential voices on the intersection of politics, culture, and society.

video_name: Kamala Harris congratulates JD Vance, hopes 'that the two can meet' at VP debate #breakingnews #news
title: NEWS TODAY
description:
Title:
Kamala Harris Congratulates JD Vance, Anticipates Potential VP Debate Showdown
https://www.foxnews.com/politics/kamala-harris-congratulates-jd-vance-hopes-that-two-can-meet-vp-debate
Summary:
Vice President Kamala Harris congratulates Senator JD Vance, R-Ohio, on his selection as former President Trump's running mate for the 2024 election. Harris expressed interest in meeting Vance in a proposed vice-presidential debate by CBS News. Known for his memoir "Hillbilly Elegy," Vance's nomination marks a significant development, potentially posing a strong challenge to Harris, who faces critiques for her communication style. The announcement came during the Republican National Convention, adding intrigue to the upcoming debates that could shape the election narrative.

Description:
In a surprising political move, Vice President Kamala Harris reached out to Senator JD Vance, R-Ohio, to congratulate him on being selected as former President Trump's running mate for the upcoming 2024 election. Harris left a message expressing her hope to meet Vance in a vice-presidential debate, which CBS News has proposed. This marks a significant moment in the race, as JD Vance, known for his memoir "Hillbilly Elegy," could pose a substantial challenge to Harris in a debate setting.

Vance's nomination was announced by Trump in a Truth Social post during the opening of the Republican National Convention. The selection has already stirred political dynamics, especially concerning the ongoing debates between President Biden and former President Trump. While no vice-presidential debate has been confirmed, the prospect of Harris facing off against Vance is seen as a potentially challenging scenario for the current Vice President.

Ashley Etienne, Harris' former communications director, noted that Vance is an incredible debater with a quality that appeals to undecided voters, making him a formidable opponent. She highlighted Vance's intelligence and quick wit as strengths that could overshadow Harris, who has occasionally been criticized for her "word salads" or rambling monologues. These characteristics have often become viral moments on social media, sometimes leading to comedic portrayals, such as on Saturday Night Live.

The possibility of a debate between Harris and Vance brings into focus the critical role of effective communication in political contests. As both parties gear up for the debates, the stakes are high, and the performances in these debates could significantly influence voter perceptions.

The Republican National Convention, where Trump officially announced Vance as his running mate, is taking place in Milwaukee, Wisconsin, from July 15-18, 2024. This event gathers delegates, politicians, and party faithful to solidify their strategies and present their candidates to the nation. Vance's entry into the race adds a new layer of excitement and uncertainty, especially with the upcoming vice-presidential debate still under negotiation.

As the political landscape continues to evolve, all eyes will be on how Harris and Vance prepare for a potential debate. The outcome could shape the narrative of the 2024 election and determine the strategies each campaign will adopt moving forward. Harris' congratulatory gesture indicates a respectful acknowledgment of Vance's entry into the race, setting the stage for a potentially historic vice-presidential contest.

video_name: Kamala Harris chỉ trích JD Vance và Trump tại sự kiện vận động ở Bắc Carolina | Quốc tế 24h
title: Quốc Tế 24h
description:
Quốc tế 24h | Kamala Harris chỉ trích JD Vance và Trump tại sự kiện vận động ở Bắc Carolina | Vào ngày 18 tháng 7, Phó Tổng thống Kamala Harris tham gia một sự kiện vận động tranh cử tại Fayetteville, Bắc Carolina, đánh dấu chuyến đi thứ 15 của bà đến tiểu bang này kể từ năm 2020. Sự kiện diễn ra khi Tổng thống Joe Biden đang cách ly vì COVID-19. Trong bài phát biểu, Harris chỉ trích cựu Tổng thống Donald Trump và Thượng nghị sĩ JD Vance, gọi dự án năm 2025 của họ là "cực đoan và gây chia rẽ", cho rằng các chính sách của họ sẽ làm sâu sắc thêm sự phân hóa xã hội.

Cuộc vận động diễn ra trong bối cảnh Biden đối mặt với áp lực từ đảng Dân chủ về việc kết thúc chiến dịch tranh cử, trong khi Trump chuẩn bị nhận đề cử của đảng Cộng hòa vào ngày 18 tháng 7. Harris đã yêu cầu JD Vance tham gia cuộc tranh luận do CBS tổ chức vào ngày 13 tháng 8. Mặc dù đã có cuộc nói chuyện giữa hai bên, nhưng các điều khoản của cuộc tranh luận vẫn chưa được thống nhất.

Việc Harris chỉ trích Trump và Vance phản ánh mối lo ngại về các chính sách cực đoan và nhấn mạnh sự cần thiết phải duy trì đoàn kết trong thời điểm khó khăn. Sự tham gia tích cực của Harris trong vận động tranh cử cho thấy vai trò quan trọng của bà trong chiến dịch tái tranh cử của Biden. Harris's chuyến đi và chỉ trích đối thủ nhấn mạnh cam kết bảo vệ các giá trị của chính quyền Biden, đồng thời phản ánh sự cần thiết phải duy trì sự ổn định và tránh xa các chính sách chia rẽ trong cuộc đua tổng thống năm tới. Kamala Harris chỉ trích JD Vance và Trump tại sự kiện vận động ở Bắc Carolina .

video_name: JD Vance Discusses the Childless Left on Tucker Carlson Tonight
title: JD Vance for Senate
description:
Ohio U.S. Senate candidate JD Vance joined Tucker Carlson on Fox News to discuss his message on the importance of promoting healthy American families - starting at the highest levels of government.

“The look at middle America - people who are actually pretty happy with their lives and the choices that they’ve made - and they hate normal Americans for choosing family over these ridiculous DC and New York status games. I think because of that, they just get so angry when someone calls it what it is.

“It’s acceptable if they ignore that it ever happens, but if someone calls out that ‘Look, if you’re a miserable cat-lady, you should not force your misery on the rest of the country’, they just get really upset about it. And I think it’s a good thing that they get upset about it. It suggests that they know that we’re hitting a nerve. Not just in this campaign, but with this message that we should invest in American families in this country. If nothing else, we should be about healthy, stable families.”

----

video_name: The Failed DEI Hires of God: Trump: J.D. Vance: Marjorie Greene: Tim Scott #kamala #trump #greene
title: MoeAI24
description:
The Failed DEI Hires of God: MAGA, Trump, and the Good Ole Boys Network
In the realm of political satire, few subjects are as ripe for parody as the MAGA movement and its leader, Donald Trump. Their latest farce? The misuse of "DEI" (diversity, equity, and inclusion) as a slur, oblivious to the nepotism and favoritism that have propelled many within their own ranks.

#### The DEI Conundrum

"DEI" is meant to represent principles that promote fairness and representation. Yet, the MAGA crowd, in their infinite wisdom, have co-opted it as a pejorative. They slap the label on Vice President Kamala Harris, implying her achievements are not due to her competence but to an imagined affirmative action. This accusation is rich with irony, considering many of these critics owe their positions to old-school nepotism and the favors of generational wealth.

#### The Failed DEI Hires of God

In this twisted narrative, we find the so-called "failed DEI hires of God" – characters like Trump, Marjorie Taylor Greene (affectionately known as "Butch" for her bleach-blonde bravado), J.D. Vance, and a parade of other MAGA rats. These figures champion meritocracy while conveniently forgetting their own gilded paths paved by connections and inherited privilege.

Congressman Maxwell Frost brilliantly encapsulated this irony on national television. 

"This is a right-wing campaign that’s going to be racist and misogynist against the vice president. But we‘re going to stand on the issues and what really matters is the fact that she is qualified," Frost told anchor Jim Acosta on "CNN Newsroom."

"They want to call her a DEI president – a DEI candidate. She has more experience than Trump and J.D. Vance combined times a million, right? She worked at the state level. She was the attorney general," he added.

#### The Hypocrisy of Unity

The Republicans love to preach unity, but they can’t even spell it, let alone grasp its meaning. They claim to unite the country, but their actions speak louder than their hollow words. Unity under MAGA? That’s as believable as Trump’s spray tan being natural.

As the MAGA rhetoric continues to unravel, we see their true colors – a party clinging to outdated tropes and manufactured outrage. The more they scream about DEI, the more they reveal their own insecurities and failures.

#### Conclusion

In this satirical universe, the MAGA movement’s obsession with DEI is nothing more than a smokescreen for their inadequacies. They can label Kamala Harris all they want, but the truth is clear: she’s more qualified than Trump and J.D. Vance combined, and no amount of MAGA spin can change that. So, as they fumble through their hypocritical chants of unity, the rest of us can sit back and enjoy the show, knowing that the joke is, and always will be, on them.

video_name: Democratic backlash over JD Vance depiction of Kamala Harris as childless cat lady
title: US NEWS UPDATE
description:
A comment by Donald Trump’s running mate JD Vance that Kamala Harris is a “childless cat lady” has triggered an angry backlash from Democrats.

Senator Vance, 39, who last week accepted the Republican Party’s nomination at its convention in Milwaukee, appeared to have made the comments on at least two instances three years ago, once during a speech to a conservative think thank and then in an interview with broadcaster Tucker Carlson, when he was still a prime time anchor for Fox News.

“The thing is that we’re effectively run in this country via the Democrats, be it via our corporate oligarchs, by a bunch of childless cat ladies who are miserable at their own lives and the choices that they’ve made, and so they want to make the rest of the country miserable too,” Senator Vance told Carlson, in the recently resurfaced interview from 2021.

video_name: ‘How Dare You!’ Whoopi Loses It On JD Vance For Attacking Kamala Harris On Not Having Children
title: AmericaNewz
description:
Whoopi Goldberg slammed Sen. JD Vance (R-OH) for mocking female lawmakers and Democrats for not giving birth to children.

During a Wednesday morning airing of The View, the panel reacted to an old Fox News segment in which Vance told Tucker Carlson that “a bunch of childless cat ladies who are miserable at their own lives” run the country.

Vance was referring to Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (D-NY) and Vice President Kamala Harris, adding that voters have “turned our country over to people who don’t really have a direct stake in it.”

Goldberg reacted to the resurfaced interview by addressing Vance directly — noting, “You never had a baby! So you know nothing about this!”

“Sir, there are people who have chosen not to have children for whatever reason. There are people who want to have children who cannot,” Goldberg responded.

She added, “How dare you! You never had a baby. Your wife had a baby, but you never had a baby. So you know nothing about this. And how dare you! And women, you heard how he thinks of you. Yeah. This is not good for you, JD!”

Former President Donald Trump recently selected Vance to be his vice presidential nominee in order to shore up support amongst voters in key states in the Midwest.

video_name: House Speaker Calls for 'Civil War' at Trump-Vance Rally If Trump Doesn't Win in November
title: BĐS T- LAND
description:
House Speaker Calls for 'Civil War' at Trump-Vance Rally If Trump Doesn't Win in November
A week after former President Donald Trump was nearly assassinated at a Pennsylvania rally, a speaker at an Ohio rally for his running mate on Monday called for "civil war" if Trump doesn't win back the White House.

"I'm afraid that if we lose this, it's going to take a civil war to save the country," Cincinnati Sen. George Lang said just before Republican vice presidential nominee JD Vance took the stage at his first solo rally in Middletown, his hometown.

Trump campaign officials did not respond to HuffPost's questions about Lang's remarks, but Lang apologized to them about a half hour later in a social media post.

“I regret the divisive comments I made in the excitement of the moment on stage. Especially in light of the assassination attempt on President Trump last week, we should all be mindful of what is said at political events, including myself,” he wrote.

The campaign of Vice President Kamala Harris, now the presumptive Democratic nominee after Joe Biden dropped out of this year’s presidential race, was quick to note that calls for violence are not new at Trump events.

“Donald Trump and JD Vance are waging a public campaign to sow hatred and promise revenge against their political opponents,” Harris campaign spokesman Ammar Moussa said in a statement. “It is a feature, not a bug, of their campaign and their message to the American people. That is why a Republican official is empowered to predict a civil war while introducing these candidates.” #news #breakingnews #trump
